# 0-AI-MANIFEST.a2ml ‚Äî Root AI manifest for 688 Attack Hub

## Purpose

This is the root AI-assistant manifest for **688 Attack Hub**, a browser
idle/strategy toy. Read this first, then
`.machine_readable/descriptiles/STATE.a2ml`, then `README.md`.

The repository is a single self-contained HTML file with no build system, no
package registry dependency, and no runtime service. There is no source tree
to navigate ‚Äî everything is in `688-attack-hub.html`.

## Where things live

- `688-attack-hub.html` ‚Äî the entire game: data (`REGIONS`, `EDGES`, `LAND`,
  `UPGRADES`, `CMS`), state (`S`), and the render/update loop (`step`,
  `paintMap`, `paintUps`, `click`, `buy`). See `ARCHITECTURE.md` for the full
  breakdown.
- `README.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md`, `EXPLAINME.adoc`, `AUDIT.adoc`,
  `AFFIRMATION.adoc`, `GOVERNANCE.adoc` ‚Äî the human documentation set.
  **`AUDIT.adoc` is authoritative on what is and isn't verified** ‚Äî this
  repo makes deliberately fewer formal claims than its sibling
  `f19-stealth-glider`, and should not be made to sound more rigorously
  verified than it is.
- `.machine_readable/` ‚Äî `descriptiles/` (STATE, META, ECOSYSTEM, AGENTIC,
  NEUROSYM, PLAYBOOK) + `contractiles/` (Must/Trust/Bust/Intend/Adjust/Dust)
  + `rsr-profile.a2ml` (declared capabilities).
- `.well-known/` ‚Äî `ai.txt`, `humans.txt`, `security.txt`.

## Invariants (read before editing)

- **This is fictional flavour, not a real network tool.** The upgrades,
  countermeasures, and "spread" mechanic are jokes about real network
  engineering (spanning-tree, DHCP, BGP hygiene), not functional exploit
  code. Do not add real target data, a real exploit primitive, or any
  network call ‚Äî doing so would falsify `AUDIT.adoc`'s central claim and
  `ci.yml`'s network/eval check would (correctly) fail the build.
- **No network calls, ever.** `ci.yml` greps for `fetch(`, `XMLHttpRequest`,
  `WebSocket`, `eval(`, `new Function(` on every push. This is load-bearing
  for the "makes no network calls" claim throughout the docs ‚Äî don't relax
  the check to make a feature pass; redesign the feature instead.
- **One self-contained file, no build step.** Do not introduce a bundler,
  a package dependency, or a static-site generator to serve the game itself
  ‚Äî `pages.yml` deploys `688-attack-hub.html` directly, by design, matching
  `f19-stealth-glider`'s proven pattern. (Neither of this estate's own SSGs,
  `ddraig-ssg` or `casket-ssg`, applies here: both render Markdown, and this
  artefact has none to render.)
- **Do not invent a verification ledger.** This repo has no
  `VERIFICATION.md` and no `src/verify*.mjs` scripts, unlike
  `f19-stealth-glider`. That is a deliberate choice recorded in
  `AUDIT.adoc`/`EXPLAINME.adoc` ‚Äî there is no comparable formal structure
  (frozen level geometry, provable lemma) to verify here. Adding aspirational
  "proof" language would be false rigor.
- Licence is AGPL-3.0-or-later for all code and docs, matching the
  `metadatastician` org convention. SPDX header as the first line of every
  `.a2ml` file; CI enforces that.
- State/metadata belongs under `.machine_readable/`, not the repository
  root. The root carries only `0-AI-MANIFEST.a2ml`.
